title: AS-205 - planned as second manned Apollo flight; cancelled in December 1966; crew re-assigned as Apollo 1 backup

images.description: early Apollo 205 crewmembers Walter M. Schirra, Jr., Donn F. Eisele and R. Walter Cunningham stand in front of the Apollo Mission Simulator at the MSC in Houston.
early Apollo 205 crewmembers Walter M. Schirra, Jr., Donn F. Eisele and R. Walter Cunningham stand in front of the Apollo Mission Simulator at the MSC in Houston.
early Apollo 205 backup crew (Borman, Stafford and Collins) during a CSM-014 equipment bench display at NAA on August 23, 1966. Borman is behind Stafford.

The prime crew for the second planned Apollo manned flight prepares for mission simulator tests at the North American Aviation plant.  (l-r) Donn F. Eisele, Senior Pilot, Walter M. Schirra, Command Pilot, and Walter Cunningham, Pilot.
